::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504002007-->
::::'''Theodoros:''' My apologies once again! Even though my shop has been around for a decade, most recent visitors have been on the lookout for my Chrysos Heir Dolia, and I've never managed to keep enough in stock.
:::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_504002008-->
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504002008-->
:::'''Theodoros:''' As for their origin, one day, while spotting Lord Phainon patrolling the city, I felt inspired and painted the epic tales of Okhema's Chrysos Heirs on a dolium.
:::'''Theodoros:''' Their courage and elegance must come from the fluttering wings of Mnestia, the Chrysalis of Gold! Their magical powder must have imbued them with such perfection!
:::'''Theodoros:''' Naturally, my dolia carry this same honor. Now, fans of the Chrysos Heirs flock to my humble shop on sale days.
:::'''Theodoros:''' Honestly, it's all a bit surreal to me. Not too long ago, I was still a struggling artist lost in my thoughts, setting up a booth on the plaza across the street, painting on dolia here and there to make ends meet.
:::'''Theodoros:''' After the frenzy over these Chrysos Heir Dolia, I opened this shop and gained some recognition. Tomorrow, I'm off to the Marmoreal Palace to paint a portrait for a distinguished elder's grand birthday bash!
:::'''Theodoros:''' However... something feels off...
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} I get where that comes from!
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504002015-->
::::'''Theodoros:''' It's remarkable to see someone as young as a new crescent moon with such profound insights into life.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Isn't it amazing to achieve both fame and fortune?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504002017-->
::::'''Theodoros:''' Well, I'm nothing special.
:::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_504002018-->
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504002018-->
:::'''Theodoros:''' ...Let's just bask in the bright light of the {{Rubi|Lucid Hour|Third of the Five Moments}} and forget the days of sorrow.
:::'''Theodoros:''' Apart from the Dolia, I also offer a range of ancient artifacts I've gathered from all over. If anything piques your interest, just let me know.
