::::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Talk}} Why did you choose to paint on dolia?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504002111-->
::::'''Theodoros:''' Because painting on dolia is one of the oldest storytelling traditions in Amphoreus. I prefer to depict ancient legends in the most traditional manner possible for that authentic touch.
::::'''Theodoros:''' Plus, pottery offers a canvas of diverse shapes and purposes, allowing me to infuse art into life. You know, I've even crafted many chimera litter trays in this city.
::::'''Theodoros:''' Maybe my dolia will be studied as antiques and relics after thousands of years. If only I could witness that day myself!
::::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Studying chimera litter trays...
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504002115-->
:::::'''Theodoros:''' Haha! My art will definitely withstand time, even if it comes with a bit of a stink.
::::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Will Amphoreus exist until then?
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504002117-->
:::::'''Theodoros:''' Oronyx's grace keeps the river of time flowing. Even if we fade away, a new civilization will eventually bud again.
:::::'''Theodoros:''' But then again, I do hope Amphoreus endures &mdash; a responsibility that rests on all esteemed Chrysos Heirs.
::::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Talk}} About our unfinished conversation from last time...
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504002120-->
::::'''Theodoros:''' I know my limits, but... praise Mnestia, chronicling the years of Amphoreus is my original inspiration. I aim to portray everything related to it, from extinct manticores to the Titans' epics, and their long-lost rituals...
::::'''Theodoros:''' But people do not currently acknowledge me due to the creations that bear my true dream... People remember me mostly for my paintings of the upper echelon of Okhema and my portrayal of the Chrysos Heirs.
::::'''Theodoros:''' While the allure of the Chrysos Heirs inspires me and I admire their divine beauty, I have to admit that practicality also played a role in my choice of clients...
::::'''Theodoros:''' Such complexity can be overwhelming at times.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
